  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>basmati rice</strong>, <strong>sultanas</strong>, <strong>half</strong> the <strong>ground turmeric</strong> (you'll use the rest later!) and 300ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[390ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[600ml]</span> <strong>cold water </strong>to a pot with a lid and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to very low and cook, covered, for 10-12 min or until all the water has absorbed and the rice is cooked</p><p>Once cooked, remove from the heat and keep covered until serving – this is your <strong>sultana rice</strong></p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1687517890987-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1687517890987-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1687517890987-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1687517890987-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1687517890987-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, drain and rinse your <strong>chickpeas</strong></p><p>Cut your <strong>lemon[s]</strong> in half</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1687517895444-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1687517895444-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1687517895444-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1687517895444-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1687517895444-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>drained chickpeas</strong> to a <strong>food processor </strong>with 3/4 of your <strong>curry powder</strong>, <strong>remaining ground turmeric</strong> and 75ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[100ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[130ml]</span> <strong>cold water</strong></p><p>Add your <strong>tahini</strong>, 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>olive oil</strong> and the juice of <strong>half</strong> your<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span><strong>lemon[s]</strong> with a very generous pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and blitz for 1-2 min or until fully combined and smooth – this is your <strong>curried hummus</strong></p><p>Cut the remaining <strong>lemon</strong> into 1 wedge per person</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1687517898635-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
