          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1687517909510-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add a small knob of <strong>butter</strong> to the <strong>cooked squash</strong> with the <strong>remaining curry powder</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and mix it all together – this is your <strong>curried squash</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1687517913551-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1687517913551-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1687517913551-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1687517913551-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1687517913551-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>curried squash </strong>with the <strong>sultana rice</strong>, <strong>curried hummus</strong>, <strong>ginger slaw</strong> and <strong>wilted</strong> <strong>spinach</strong> to the side</p><p>Garnish with a <strong>lemon wedge</strong>, <strong>flaked almonds</strong> and <strong>coriander leaves</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8,
